com.martinandersson.javaee.utils

Interface ThreadScheduler.Yielder

  • Enclosing class:
    ThreadScheduler
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface ThreadScheduler.Yielder
    A yielder provide method yield() that a stage may invoke to "yield" and let another stage begin or resume his execution path until that thread yield or die.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void yield()
      Yield the calling thread's use of CPU to the next stage ready to execute.

    • Method Detail

      • yield

        void yield()
        Yield the calling thread's use of CPU to the next stage ready to execute.

        This method has no effect if there is no other stages left to execute.

        It is imperative that client code must not try-catch exceptions caused by this method. Doing so may have a detrimental effect on the runtime behavior of ThreadScheduler.

        See Also:
        ThreadScheduler, ThreadScheduler.Yielder
